laxy and none in the LMC. Hence the\nexclusion of an GC origin challenges the SMBH paradigm. We conclude that there\nmust be other mechanism(s) to accelerate stars to hyper-velocity speed than the\nSMBH. We draw attention to dynamical ejection from dense massive clusters, that\nhas recently been proposed by Gvaramadze et al. (2008).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 29 Jan 2008 10:20:26 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
